credit.credit-words: were whol y unlike the traditions and dogmas taught by the rabbis. There was a freshness, a life and vigor, in His sayings;
"The truths that came from the lips of the Divine Teacher
they came home to the mind with a clearness and power that captivated His hearers.
God's workers are to learn the same manner of teaching. They are to bring to men truths ful of fragrance,
like fresh flowers from the garden of God's word."
THY WORD IS LIKE A GARDEN
